1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 24=

3
00:01:28,020 --> 00:01:31,940
(Agent)

4
00:01:31,950 --> 00:01:33,510
Come on.

5
00:01:34,480 --> 00:01:36,040
Here, over here.

6
00:01:38,630 --> 00:01:39,510
Hello.

7
00:01:39,510 --> 00:01:41,230
Where are you, Mr. Xiu?

8
00:01:41,230 --> 00:01:42,400
We're waiting for you to record.

9
00:01:43,070 --> 00:01:45,040
Find someone else. I can't sing.

10
00:01:45,350 --> 00:01:47,310
That female lead's pretty talented.

11
00:01:47,310 --> 00:01:48,430
She looks good.

12
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:50,920
Yeah, I've met her before.

13
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:52,150
She's got a killer body.

14
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:56,760
To be honest,

15
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:58,920
I'm hitting on her right now.

16
00:01:58,920 --> 00:02:00,920
She doesn't seem easy to win over.

17
00:02:00,920 --> 00:02:02,510
Oh, really?

18
00:02:02,510 --> 00:02:04,710
She's classy and cool as ice.

19
00:02:04,710 --> 00:02:05,550
Exactly.

20
00:02:05,730 --> 00:02:06,590
Eh.

21
00:02:06,590 --> 00:02:08,120
What's her name again?

22
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,150
I think it's…

23
00:02:10,470 --> 00:02:11,470
Luanluan.

24
00:02:11,910 --> 00:02:13,630
Luanluan.

25
00:02:14,470 --> 00:02:16,840
You rube.

26
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:17,840
You know what.

27
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,310
She acts all saintly most of the time.

28
00:02:21,310 --> 00:02:22,430
But actually…

29
00:02:22,750 --> 00:02:24,120
She's a homewrecker.

30
00:02:25,090 --> 00:02:26,520
And she's the one chasing after him.

31
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:27,840
Even with all that.

32
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,080
You're still hitting on her?

33
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,630
Haven't locked it down yet?

34
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:32,870
That premiere night.

35
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,560
We're having a wrap party.

36
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:37,310
Me and her…

37
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:40,190
We almost kissed.

38
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,310
Whoa.

39
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,710
Hey.

40
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,030
But even then, she…

41
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:45,560
She still puts on a prude act
with me here.

42
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:49,470
All that talk,
and you still didn't get her.

43
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:06,280
Mom.

44
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:07,800
We're on our way.

45
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,190
Have you reached the hospital?

46
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:11,470
Sir, please drive faster.

47
00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:13,430
Okay okay, sure.

48
00:03:13,430 --> 00:03:14,430
Don't panic first.

49
00:03:14,490 --> 00:03:16,120
When you get to the hospital,
call me anytime

50
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:17,360
if you have any problems.

51
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,680
We'll be there soon.

52
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,150
Alright, okay.

53
00:03:22,590 --> 00:03:24,190
How did he just pass out?

54
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:26,430
He was fine last time I saw him.

55
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:28,120
Don't worry, he'll be okay.

56
00:03:42,540 --> 00:03:43,820
(In Surgery; Operating Room)

57
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:44,680
Hey.

58
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:46,080
Why did you take so long?

59
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,190
Why do you smell like cigarettes?

60
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:51,470
Where were you drinking
so late at night?

61
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:52,840
You're just like your dad.

62
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,960
Neither of you ever let me rest easy.

63
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:57,310
How did you get here?

64
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:58,840
Don't worry, aunt. We took a cab.

65
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,360
- Oh.
- How is he?

66
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:02,560
He insisted on drinking a can of beer
before bed.

67
00:04:02,710 --> 00:04:03,960
I was brushing my teeth.

68
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:05,240
I turned around, and…

69
00:04:05,430 --> 00:04:06,520
He collapsed

70
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:08,030
before he even opened the fridge.

71
00:04:08,030 --> 00:04:09,800
Didn't he get a checkup at my place?

72
00:04:10,190 --> 00:04:11,360
Wasn't it all fine?

73
00:04:11,360 --> 00:04:13,280
Your dad told me not to tell you.

74
00:04:13,420 --> 00:04:14,840
He was afraid it'd mess with your work.

75
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:17,430
Well, he's been feeling
under the weather lately.

76
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:19,070
So we came to the hospital early.

77
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:20,920
After the checkup, the doctor said he…

78
00:04:21,070 --> 00:04:22,360
has some blood vessel blockage.

79
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:23,830
Told him to get a minor surgery.

80
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,830
But your dad's so stubborn, he refused.

81
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,000
(In Surgery)
Said he knows his own body best.

82
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:30,360
And now this. Look at him.

83
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:34,750
- Family members.
- Yes yes.

84
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:36,160
The patient is out of danger.

85
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:37,510
He'll be taken to the ward shortly.

86
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:41,270
Ow.

87
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:50,100
(Ward 01)

88
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,160
Want to step out for a bit?

89
00:05:58,830 --> 00:05:59,670
Mm.

90
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,360
How's aunt doing?

91
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,800
She's dead set on
waiting for him to wake up.

92
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,510
The doctor said it'll take some time.

93
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,120
I told her to go home
and grab some toiletries.

94
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,360
She can take over for us tomorrow.

95
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:19,950
That's when she left.

96
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,390
My mom…

97
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:25,750
She's the most stubborn person ever.

98
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:28,720
Looks tough on the outside.

99
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:31,430
But she's panicking inside.

100
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,160
Alright, don't act tough.

101
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,560
You're no better.

102
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:53,560
If you want to cry,

103
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,080
just let it out.

104
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:57,840
Get lost.

105
00:06:59,630 --> 00:07:00,630
Who wants to cry?

106
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:12,630
(Li Xiaoxi)
(Where are you?)

107
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,750
(Why aren't you answering my calls?)

108
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,000
(Gong and I went back to his hometown.)

109
00:07:17,270 --> 00:07:18,110
(We're at the hospital.)

110
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:19,630
(His dad suddenly passed out.)

111
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,940
(But he's out of danger now.)

112
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:22,100
(Bei)
(Don't worry.)

113
00:07:33,100 --> 00:07:34,360
(Bei)
(Give me a few more days.)

114
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,270
Luanluan.

115
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:00,160
Luanluan, open the door, Luanluan.

116
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:01,680
I'm sorry.

117
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,430
I'm a jerk.

118
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:06,120
I'm the worst person ever.

119
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,070
I'm sorry, Luanluan.

120
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,800
Open the door, I'm begging you.

121
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,600
That night you called.

122
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:18,720
Did that man mess with you?

123
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,200
I'm sorry.

124
00:08:21,870 --> 00:08:23,000
What are you doing?

125
00:08:26,390 --> 00:08:27,510
What do you want?

126
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,480
Want me to cry with you?

127
00:08:31,640 --> 00:08:32,480
Want me to tell you

128
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:34,080
I'm touched that you came to see me?

129
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,790
I'm really sorry.

130
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:39,120
That day…

131
00:08:40,630 --> 00:08:42,240
When you called that day…

132
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:45,600
I shouldn't have said those things.

133
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:46,870
If that's all this is about.

134
00:08:46,870 --> 00:08:48,000
I accept your apology.

135
00:08:49,200 --> 00:08:50,040
And then what?

136
00:08:55,030 --> 00:08:56,960
Have you ever thought
why things got like this?

137
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:01,000
You've been hiding everywhere
all this time.

138
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:04,000
You want love and understanding.

139
00:09:04,750 --> 00:09:05,720
You found me.

140
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,720
Got what you wanted from me.

141
00:09:08,390 --> 00:09:10,120
Then you felt guilty about her.

142
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,600
You keep running from your own desires.

143
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,390
Afraid to make a decision.

144
00:09:18,380 --> 00:09:19,240
You paint yourself as

145
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,870
a victim of marriage.

146
00:09:20,870 --> 00:09:22,390
Because victims are forced.

147
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,680
Helpless.

148
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,120
No need to take responsibility.

149
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,320
I always thought.

150
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,000
I could give you strength.

151
00:09:32,840 --> 00:09:34,440
And I was even proud of that.

152
00:09:39,150 --> 00:09:40,200
Now I realize

153
00:09:42,240 --> 00:09:43,550
strength comes from within.

154
00:09:44,050 --> 00:09:45,150
No one else can give it to you.

155
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:53,870
I'm sorry. I won't wait for you anymore.

156
00:10:29,790 --> 00:10:30,910
Do you remember?

157
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,360
When I was eight years old,

158
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,630
I put a stink bug

159
00:10:38,630 --> 00:10:39,600
on grandpa's birthday cake.

160
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:42,440
You slapped me right across the face.

161
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:47,790
After that,

162
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:49,240
I've been defying you.

163
00:10:50,630 --> 00:10:52,120
I made you mad so many times.

164
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:56,000
And got slapped by you so many times.

165
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:02,270
All these years,

166
00:11:03,550 --> 00:11:04,870
you can't hit me anymore.

167
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,750
But your words never stop.

168
00:11:10,910 --> 00:11:12,550
I actually like it when you scold me.

169
00:11:26,670 --> 00:11:27,510
Dad.

170
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:33,630
Let's not stay here.

171
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:36,150
Let's not rest here, okay?

172
00:11:37,390 --> 00:11:38,600
Lying here too long.

173
00:11:39,150 --> 00:11:40,670
It'll take a toll on your body.

174
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:46,030
Did I make you mad?

175
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:47,750
Wake up.

176
00:11:49,270 --> 00:11:50,550
Slap me a couple more times.

177
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:52,720
Scold me a little more.

178
00:11:53,910 --> 00:11:54,790
Alright?

179
00:12:26,860 --> 00:12:31,340
(Ward)

180
00:12:34,790 --> 00:12:35,630
Alright, alright.

181
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:39,390
I've been up all night, just nodded off.

182
00:12:39,830 --> 00:12:40,680
Where's Bei?

183
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:41,610
Bei?

184
00:12:41,610 --> 00:12:43,080
Oh, my head, you know what?

185
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:45,270
I packed all my stuff
and my clean clothes.

186
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:46,790
Left them there,
then forgot on my way out.

187
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:48,510
I sent Bei back to get them.

188
00:12:49,620 --> 00:12:52,220
(Ward)

189
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,320
Why are you here?

190
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:55,080
Did my silly son tell you?

191
00:12:55,480 --> 00:12:56,600
How's uncle doing?

192
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:59,150
He's out of danger now,
still unconscious.

193
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:01,270
Eh.

194
00:13:01,270 --> 00:13:02,870
Uh, this is…

195
00:13:03,200 --> 00:13:04,080
Hello, aunt.

196
00:13:04,550 --> 00:13:05,550
I'm Li Xiaoxi.

197
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,120
Ah, Li Xiaoxi.

198
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,080
Li Xiaoxi is...

199
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:10,270
Who's that?

200
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,320
Hey, hey.

201
00:13:17,790 --> 00:13:18,630
You're awake.

202
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:19,750
You scared me to death.

203
00:13:20,220 --> 00:13:22,060
(Ward)

204
00:13:22,080 --> 00:13:23,030
You're doing well.

205
00:13:23,030 --> 00:13:25,150
Get some rest, you'll recover soon.

206
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:27,270
This is very common, don't worry.

207
00:13:27,480 --> 00:13:29,440
You can recover with medication

208
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:32,150
and rehabilitation training later.

209
00:13:32,510 --> 00:13:34,000
But it'll take some time.

210
00:13:34,390 --> 00:13:35,360
Don't be in a hurry.

211
00:13:36,570 --> 00:13:38,150
- Thank you, doctor.
- Thanks, doctor.

212
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,600
Take the medicine before 2 PM.

213
00:13:39,600 --> 00:13:40,790
Okay, okay.

214
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:41,670
Hey.

215
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:42,630
I'm telling you.

216
00:13:42,630 --> 00:13:45,270
(Ward)
The doctor said this is normal.

217
00:13:45,270 --> 00:13:47,750
You'll recover, don't worry.

218
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:48,720
Don't worry.

219
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:51,150
Stop shouting. I can hear you.

220
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:53,360
You can hear me? Good, good.

221
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:55,270
Let me wash your face.

222
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:57,480
Time to eat.

223
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,510
What did he say?

224
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:01,960
Time to eat.

225
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:03,670
Uncle said it's time to eat.

226
00:14:03,670 --> 00:14:04,550
Eat, eat.

227
00:14:04,550 --> 00:14:06,080
Come on, let's eat.

228
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,360
Here, give it to me.

229
00:14:07,670 --> 00:14:08,510
Hey.

230
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,080
Here, here.

231
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:14,320
I'll go get some hot water.

232
00:14:14,630 --> 00:14:15,750
Aunt, let me help you.

233
00:14:16,180 --> 00:14:17,030
Sure.

234
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:17,870
Then I'll

235
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:19,870
wash this towel.

236
00:14:22,630 --> 00:14:24,030
Eat more.

237
00:14:31,270 --> 00:14:32,480
Ah, here.

238
00:14:36,030 --> 00:14:36,870
Here.

239
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:44,120
Slow down.

240
00:15:08,390 --> 00:15:09,230
Here.

241
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,320
Here.

242
00:15:43,550 --> 00:15:44,910
My dad's always

243
00:15:45,150 --> 00:15:46,120
been in great shape.

244
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,870
Runs 5 kilometers in 30 minutes.

245
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:50,750
I can't even keep up with him.

246
00:15:51,620 --> 00:15:53,030
Climbs five flights of stairs in one go.

247
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:54,320
No huffing.

248
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:57,080
A few years ago,

249
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,480
if I made him mad,

250
00:16:00,910 --> 00:16:02,120
he might punch me twice.

251
00:16:03,390 --> 00:16:04,720
He can't do that anymore these years.

252
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:08,150
But his mouth's still just as bad.

253
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,030
Sometimes when he scolds me,

254
00:16:11,030 --> 00:16:12,360
I can't even get a word in.

255
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,440
You mean
there's a time you can't talk back?

256
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:22,000
Watching him eat porridge just now.

257
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:26,920
You know.

258
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:28,920
My heart…

259
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,030
Don't worry.

260
00:16:33,790 --> 00:16:34,840
Didn't the doctor say

261
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:35,870
this is all temporary?

262
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:39,360
Uncle will definitely get better.

263
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:42,750
He'll be as lively as before.

264
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:45,750
Sometimes I think I'm such a jerk.

265
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:51,550
Last time he went to the Third Hospital.

266
00:16:53,910 --> 00:16:55,120
I just couldn't stand him.

267
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,240
And he felt the same about me,
of course.

268
00:16:58,910 --> 00:17:00,030
Then he suddenly said,

269
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:01,840
"Why aren't you married yet?"

270
00:17:04,110 --> 00:17:05,550
I snapped back with a sharp line.

271
00:17:08,960 --> 00:17:09,800
I told him,

272
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:15,400
"Not only will you not see me

273
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,550
get married in your lifetime.

274
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:22,400
I might not even

275
00:17:22,550 --> 00:17:24,750
see it in mine."

276
00:17:27,440 --> 00:17:28,720
Pretty lousy, right?

277
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:31,640
My parents nag me about marriage too.

278
00:17:32,790 --> 00:17:34,310
I just tune them out after a few words.

279
00:17:35,480 --> 00:17:36,640
But this is...

280
00:17:37,480 --> 00:17:39,270
He was fine just a while ago.

281
00:17:39,590 --> 00:17:41,400
How come there are so many forms?

282
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:42,680
Don't be sad.

283
00:17:46,070 --> 00:17:46,920
It's fine.

284
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,070
I'm not crying.

285
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,240
I'm just expressing my feelings.

286
00:18:03,440 --> 00:18:05,160
Can I borrow your shoulder for a sec?

287
00:18:14,480 --> 00:18:15,350
I've never seen you cry.

288
00:18:15,350 --> 00:18:16,640
I'm kinda embarrassed.

289
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,680
No wonder your heart's beating so fast.

290
00:18:22,830 --> 00:18:24,110
I don't have any tissues with me.

291
00:18:25,070 --> 00:18:27,000
Just wipe your nose with your sleeve.

292
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:42,390
Harder.

293
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:45,830
Alright, let me wipe
the sweat off your hands.

294
00:18:47,140 --> 00:18:48,510
Hey, you know.

295
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,400
You didn't even see it.

296
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,750
You know, they were so sweet.

297
00:18:52,750 --> 00:18:54,030
The two of them just now...

298
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:55,830
hugged each other!

299
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,080
Hugged.

300
00:18:57,270 --> 00:18:58,480
Hugged each other?

301
00:18:58,480 --> 00:18:59,680
They almost...

302
00:18:59,880 --> 00:19:01,160
kiss!

303
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:05,880
I'm telling you, this girl

304
00:19:06,310 --> 00:19:07,750
seems really nice.

305
00:19:08,070 --> 00:19:09,400
And she's pretty too.

306
00:19:09,830 --> 00:19:11,790
You can rest easy this time.

307
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:12,880
Yeah.

308
00:19:14,590 --> 00:19:15,750
- Rest easy.
- Not bad.

309
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:16,960
Pretty good.

310
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,880
You need to eat more.

311
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,830
Eating more will
help you recover faster.

312
00:19:21,960 --> 00:19:24,310
Give you more energy, got it?

313
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:26,310
What's the topic? So happy over there?

314
00:19:26,310 --> 00:19:28,480
- Ya, you're back.
- Feeling better?

315
00:19:29,150 --> 00:19:30,000
Aunt.

316
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:30,840
Hello.

317
00:19:32,510 --> 00:19:34,550
Go up there. You sit here.

318
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:35,550
Me? I sit here?

319
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:36,510
Yes, take a seat.

320
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:40,760
Xiaoxi.

321
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:42,510
What's your zodiac sign?

322
00:19:42,920 --> 00:19:44,310
Why are you asking her that?

323
00:19:44,310 --> 00:19:45,270
Trying to read her fortune?

324
00:19:45,270 --> 00:19:47,310
You shouldn't ask a girl her age.

325
00:19:47,310 --> 00:19:48,160
Just ask her zodiac sign.

326
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,640
I can guess it myself.

327
00:19:49,640 --> 00:19:51,480
What's her zodiac sign to you?

328
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,070
Can't you talk nicely?

329
00:19:53,070 --> 00:19:54,590
I'm asking Xiaoxi.

330
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:56,480
Why are you interrupting?

331
00:19:56,830 --> 00:19:58,030
Aunt, I'm a Rooster.

332
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,000
Rooster.

333
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:01,310
Rooster.

334
00:20:01,310 --> 00:20:02,200
Daughter-in-law.

335
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,160
Daughter-in-law.

336
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:07,030
I understood that word.

337
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,350
Oh!

338
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:09,880
Daughter-in-law.

339
00:20:10,030 --> 00:20:12,030
Mom, what are you saying? She's…

340
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:13,310
I'm not talking nonsense.

341
00:20:13,310 --> 00:20:15,480
Look, you two look perfect together.

342
00:20:15,480 --> 00:20:17,000
Match? Oh my goodness.

343
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,510
How long have you two been together?

344
00:20:18,600 --> 00:20:19,640
Aunt, you're misunderstanding.

345
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,750
We're just good friends.

346
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:21,720
Misunderstand what?

347
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,240
I saw you two outside just now,

348
00:20:23,240 --> 00:20:24,310
hugging and kissing.

349
00:20:24,310 --> 00:20:25,400
Who was hugging and kissing?

350
00:20:25,400 --> 00:20:27,110
I told your dad all about it.

351
00:20:27,110 --> 00:20:28,030
Told him when I got back.

352
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:29,350
He was over the moon.

353
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,790
Me and my husband, you know?

354
00:20:31,960 --> 00:20:34,750
We started out as good friends too.

355
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,350
Aunt.

356
00:20:36,350 --> 00:20:37,720
Here, I brought your stuff.

357
00:20:37,720 --> 00:20:39,270
Thanks, really appreciate it.

358
00:20:39,270 --> 00:20:40,480
Uncle, rest well.

359
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,750
Got stuff to do. I'll be back tonight.

360
00:20:42,790 --> 00:20:44,310
- Bei, you're leaving?
- Aunt, I'm leaving.

361
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:45,160
Hit me up if you need.

362
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,000
- Bei, take care.
- Let's eat together.

363
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,640
Meal. Calling you for a meal.

364
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,480
This…

365
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,960
Wait, why are you...

366
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:54,880
Why did she leave too? What's happening?

367
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:56,260
What do you think?

368
00:20:56,260 --> 00:20:57,110
Huh?

369
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:58,160
What do I think?

370
00:20:58,920 --> 00:21:00,750
What's going on?

371
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,400
Told you not to talk nonsense.

372
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:06,140
She's Bei's girlfriend.

373
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:07,000
Ah?

374
00:21:07,010 --> 00:21:07,860
Huh?

375
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:09,720
Your…

376
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,000
Girlfriend?

377
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,590
Yeah, my girlfriend.

378
00:21:13,590 --> 00:21:14,680
We're getting married soon.

379
00:21:14,880 --> 00:21:15,720
Mm.

380
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,550
So did Bei hear

381
00:21:17,550 --> 00:21:19,550
everything I said in there?

382
00:21:19,550 --> 00:21:20,920
With all that noise, who wouldn't hear?

383
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:21,880
They can hear you downstairs.

384
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,000
- What?
- Oh no.

385
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:24,480
W... what

386
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,270
noise?

387
00:21:27,070 --> 00:21:29,310
Once you're better,
we'll have the wedding.

388
00:21:29,310 --> 00:21:30,480
A hundred tables.

389
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:33,880
Okay, okay.

390
00:21:33,880 --> 00:21:34,720
Okay.

391
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:36,840
Wait.

392
00:21:42,510 --> 00:21:43,830
Are you avoiding me?

393
00:21:45,750 --> 00:21:46,640
No.

394
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:47,480
No?

395
00:21:49,110 --> 00:21:51,110
You didn't even
look at me just now inside.

396
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:53,550
I felt like I was invisible.

397
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,480
Bei, I think...

398
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,550
I think we need to have a proper talk.

399
00:22:03,780 --> 00:22:05,200
I don't want to talk about this
right now.

400
00:22:06,640 --> 00:22:07,920
Then when?

401
00:22:09,240 --> 00:22:10,750
I panic every single day you're gone.

402
00:22:10,750 --> 00:22:11,830
I don't want it to be like this.

403
00:22:13,550 --> 00:22:14,720
That's why I came here.

404
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:19,160
This isn't just about you.

405
00:22:19,160 --> 00:22:20,720
I want to know
what's really on your mind.

406
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:24,550
There's a lot I haven't told you.

407
00:22:25,350 --> 00:22:26,400
It's not that I don't want to.

408
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:28,350
You have to give me
a chance to say them.

409
00:22:31,030 --> 00:22:32,680
I'd rather you got mad at me!

410
00:22:33,350 --> 00:22:34,720
Than act like this now.

411
00:22:36,510 --> 00:22:37,350
It's like…

412
00:22:37,930 --> 00:22:39,680
I've been shut out of your world
all of a sudden.

413
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,590
I told you.

414
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:42,440
My head's a total mess right now.

415
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:44,640
Let's talk later.

416
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:48,270
You plan to leave me here alone?

417
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,200
Isn't Gong here?

418
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:04,790
What do you mean?

419
00:23:36,240 --> 00:23:37,200
Today...

420
00:23:39,200 --> 00:23:40,070
Thank you.

421
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:44,640
You're being so polite today.

422
00:23:45,350 --> 00:23:46,440
It's weird.

423
00:23:48,920 --> 00:23:50,350
Seeing you cry today

424
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,270
made me think a lot.

425
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:54,880
From now on, if something happens,

426
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,160
don't keep it bottled up.

427
00:23:56,830 --> 00:23:57,750
Just say it out loud.

428
00:23:59,270 --> 00:24:00,680
Otherwise, we'll regret it.

429
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,830
You and Mr. Bei…

430
00:24:06,680 --> 00:24:08,480
He felt so strange to me today.

431
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:11,920
Maybe I never truly knew him.

432
00:24:14,510 --> 00:24:15,510
Mr. Bei.

433
00:24:16,480 --> 00:24:17,550
He's just that type of person.

434
00:24:17,830 --> 00:24:19,350
He keeps everything inside.

435
00:24:19,750 --> 00:24:21,030
Carries the burden alone.

436
00:24:21,310 --> 00:24:23,070
He looks calm
and in control on the outside,

437
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,030
but maybe he's
crying somewhere in secret.

438
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:29,160
He asked me to give him some time.

439
00:24:30,440 --> 00:24:31,550
But I'm scared...

440
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:33,240
If he wanted to leave you,

441
00:24:33,590 --> 00:24:34,960
he wouldn't be acting like this.

442
00:24:35,270 --> 00:24:36,110
On the contrary,

443
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,790
he's more scared than anyone
that the people around him will leave.

444
00:24:40,510 --> 00:24:41,720
There are things

445
00:24:42,030 --> 00:24:43,640
that he should really say himself.

446
00:24:44,480 --> 00:24:46,350
But you know what he's like.

447
00:24:46,350 --> 00:24:47,550
Even with a knife to his throat,

448
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:48,880
he wouldn't say a word.

449
00:24:50,790 --> 00:24:52,000
His parents got divorced.

450
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:53,590
He was raised by his grandmother.

451
00:24:53,590 --> 00:24:54,430
You knew that?

452
00:24:55,030 --> 00:24:55,870
Mm.

453
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:57,110
He's mentioned it before.

454
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:59,830
His dad was always
away on business trips.

455
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:01,440
When he was little,

456
00:25:01,880 --> 00:25:04,000
he knew his mom wasn't happy.

457
00:25:04,830 --> 00:25:06,550
So he tried to do everything right.

458
00:25:06,550 --> 00:25:08,680
Just hoping it would
make her smile again.

459
00:25:10,110 --> 00:25:11,030
Come back!

460
00:25:17,270 --> 00:25:18,110
Hang in there.

461
00:25:20,070 --> 00:25:20,910
Lift it up.

462
00:25:21,310 --> 00:25:22,200
Straighten your back.

463
00:25:28,480 --> 00:25:29,320
You two.

464
00:25:30,160 --> 00:25:31,000
Ready.

465
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:02,830
Done training?

466
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:05,110
Hey, you're drenched in sweat.

467
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,480
Come on, wipe it off.

468
00:26:10,790 --> 00:26:11,920
My son is amazing.

469
00:26:12,200 --> 00:26:13,200
I saw you running

470
00:26:13,200 --> 00:26:14,070
just now.

471
00:26:14,310 --> 00:26:16,070
The coach said
I can represent the school

472
00:26:16,070 --> 00:26:17,550
at the Student Sports Meet.

473
00:26:17,830 --> 00:26:19,000
100-meter sprint, 200-meter sprint

474
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:20,350
and the 4x100 relay.

475
00:26:20,590 --> 00:26:21,640
That's a lot.

476
00:26:22,550 --> 00:26:24,070
The coach let you join,

477
00:26:24,100 --> 00:26:26,070
so it means you're the fastest
in the whole school, right?

478
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:27,320
Mm.

479
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:28,750
Alright.

480
00:26:29,310 --> 00:26:30,960
I'll cook you
some stir-fried pork at home.

481
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:34,750
You've worked hard.

482
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,310
I'm holding it together for the family.

483
00:26:36,310 --> 00:26:37,310
Do you think it's easy for me?

484
00:26:37,620 --> 00:26:39,830
What responsibility have you taken
for this family all these years?

485
00:26:40,270 --> 00:26:41,790
You weren't there
when our son was bullied.

486
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:44,180
You weren't there
when I had surgery.

487
00:26:44,750 --> 00:26:46,590
You didn't even come back
when your dad died.

488
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:48,510
I'm the daughter-in-law.

489
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:51,110
I wore mourning clothes and
took care of the funeral all by myself.

490
00:26:51,110 --> 00:26:52,200
Why?

491
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:55,160
You made up an excuse to go off
and have fun.

492
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,200
Left this huge mess to me.

493
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,480
If I hadn't swallowed my pride
to borrow money,

494
00:26:59,480 --> 00:27:00,830
how would our son and I get by?

495
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:02,510
Tell me how!

496
00:27:03,830 --> 00:27:05,440
My words are harsh.

497
00:27:05,440 --> 00:27:07,000
But isn't it the truth?

498
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:10,030
Don't give me that nonsense!

499
00:27:13,400 --> 00:27:15,200
He's always been scared
his mom would leave his dad,

500
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,270
and leave him too.

501
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:27,800
Mom.

502
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:31,040
Mom.

503
00:27:39,400 --> 00:27:41,550
Oh, you ran out without shoes.

504
00:27:41,750 --> 00:27:43,640
Hurry put on your shoes,
wash your hands and eat.

505
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,270
Eat slowly.

506
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:53,400
Don't stress about the race today.

507
00:27:53,680 --> 00:27:54,920
Just run like you always do.

508
00:27:55,350 --> 00:27:57,400
I'll be at the sports field
cheering for you.

509
00:27:58,070 --> 00:28:00,350
Do you remember what events I'm in?

510
00:28:00,550 --> 00:28:01,720
100-meter sprint, 200-meter sprint

511
00:28:01,720 --> 00:28:03,110
and the 4x100 relay, right?

512
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:04,880
Testing me, huh.

513
00:28:05,720 --> 00:28:07,000
Mm, wait a sec.

514
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,400
Ta-da!

515
00:28:12,960 --> 00:28:13,880
Guess what this is?

516
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:15,720
Come on, take a look.

517
00:28:18,270 --> 00:28:19,400
Do you like it?

518
00:28:19,400 --> 00:28:20,240
I like it.

519
00:28:20,920 --> 00:28:22,400
Come on, let me help you try it on.

520
00:28:23,750 --> 00:28:25,310
You have to win first place.

521
00:28:25,750 --> 00:28:27,750
I'll be there to
watch you get the award.

522
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:29,840
Come on, push hard.

523
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,960
I knew my baby is the best.

524
00:29:18,350 --> 00:29:19,830
You have to win first place.

525
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:22,200
I'll be there to
watch you get the award.

526
00:29:37,920 --> 00:29:39,400
Mom, I'm home.

527
00:29:57,680 --> 00:29:58,520
Mom!

528
00:30:01,880 --> 00:30:02,720
Mom!

529
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:09,160
Mom!

530
00:30:13,510 --> 00:30:15,030
When he was a kid, he thought

531
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:18,590
his mom left

532
00:30:18,790 --> 00:30:20,440
because he didn't win first place.

533
00:30:21,590 --> 00:30:22,790
So ever since then,

534
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:25,000
he worked hard to do everything better.

535
00:30:25,750 --> 00:30:27,510
Scared that the people around him
would leave.

536
00:30:28,070 --> 00:30:29,350
It makes him so miserable.

537
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,000
Ever since then,

538
00:30:36,310 --> 00:30:37,790
whenever he disappears.

539
00:30:38,270 --> 00:30:39,160
I know

540
00:30:39,160 --> 00:30:40,640
he's gone to run at that playground.

541
00:30:43,200 --> 00:30:44,680
When he's uneasy,

542
00:30:45,070 --> 00:30:46,310
he'll run like crazy.

543
00:30:46,790 --> 00:30:48,110
Until he's completely exhausted.

544
00:30:48,590 --> 00:30:50,030
He acts like a madman.

545
00:30:50,590 --> 00:30:51,720
Honestly, I think…

546
00:30:52,640 --> 00:30:54,640
he just lacks a sense of
security deep down.

547
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:03,960
Be gentle, be gentle.

548
00:31:04,310 --> 00:31:05,720
Be gentle.

549
00:31:07,110 --> 00:31:08,790
Alright, alright, let me do it.

550
00:31:19,400 --> 00:31:20,680
You old fool.

551
00:31:22,200 --> 00:31:24,270
I never had a comfortable day with you.

552
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,680
Even now I'm still looking after you.

553
00:31:28,590 --> 00:31:29,880
So in my past life,

554
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:30,960
I owed the two of you?

555
00:31:31,310 --> 00:31:32,270
Now I'm stuck with you guys.

556
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:35,040
Mom.

557
00:31:37,510 --> 00:31:38,590
Do you love dad?

558
00:31:41,920 --> 00:31:43,720
Ever since I can remember,

559
00:31:44,160 --> 00:31:45,830
you two argued all day and night.

560
00:31:46,550 --> 00:31:48,350
Over the tiniest, most trivial things.

561
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:49,960
Said the worst things to each other.

562
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,790
It was so annoying
I didn't want to go home.

563
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,110
Well,

564
00:31:55,790 --> 00:31:57,110
dad's already like this now.

565
00:31:57,350 --> 00:31:58,590
And you still criticize him.

566
00:31:59,070 --> 00:32:01,030
Why did you even marry him then?

567
00:32:01,880 --> 00:32:03,110
What's the point?

568
00:32:04,270 --> 00:32:05,720
You don't get it at all.

569
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:09,270
Well, your dad

570
00:32:09,920 --> 00:32:10,920
is hard of hearing.

571
00:32:12,070 --> 00:32:14,270
He can't catch what people are saying.

572
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,680
And the less he hears.

573
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:18,920
The less he wants to talk to anyone.

574
00:32:19,200 --> 00:32:20,070
Every day,

575
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:22,720
he just curls up on that couch
staring at his phone.

576
00:32:22,880 --> 00:32:24,480
If I don't bicker with him a little,

577
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:26,200
he'll get Alzheimer's disease.

578
00:32:27,200 --> 00:32:28,240
Arguing with him

579
00:32:28,240 --> 00:32:29,640
is a skill.

580
00:32:29,830 --> 00:32:31,480
And you can't hurt his pride.

581
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:34,270
Otherwise, you know,
he'll really get upset.

582
00:32:34,270 --> 00:32:36,400
He's… he's a big kid now.

583
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,400
Come on, take a nap.

584
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,110
Well, the other day,

585
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,680
I found a notebook.

586
00:32:47,830 --> 00:32:49,550
Ah, it's been over ten years.

587
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:50,830
Over ten years.

588
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:52,760
It had...

589
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:54,550
a sentence written in it.

590
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:57,440
Today…

591
00:32:58,000 --> 00:32:59,240
I feel really awful.

592
00:33:00,350 --> 00:33:01,830
I just can't get past it.

593
00:33:02,310 --> 00:33:03,270
I keep wondering.

594
00:33:03,550 --> 00:33:04,440
Back then…

595
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,960
What happened that day?

596
00:33:05,960 --> 00:33:07,070
That made me feel so bad.

597
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:09,000
No matter how I try, I can't recall.

598
00:33:10,310 --> 00:33:11,510
But there's one thing…

599
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:15,200
When your dad and I got married,

600
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:18,070
he gave me a faded washbasin.

601
00:33:18,270 --> 00:33:19,680
It was bright red.

602
00:33:20,510 --> 00:33:22,160
I was over the moon back then.

603
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:23,640
Just that one thing.

604
00:33:23,660 --> 00:33:24,500
All my life,

605
00:33:24,510 --> 00:33:26,310
every time I think of it,
I can't help but smile.

606
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:30,240
Well, your dad and I

607
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,960
argued our whole lives.

608
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,720
But looking back now,

609
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:36,000
there was never any real resentment.

610
00:33:38,070 --> 00:33:38,910
Now

611
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:40,640
after everything,

612
00:33:40,640 --> 00:33:42,070
he falls sick. I have to look after him.

613
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:45,590
Life

614
00:33:46,480 --> 00:33:47,480
is just like

615
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,240
picking corn.

616
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,830
Grabbing one while dropping another.

617
00:33:52,270 --> 00:33:54,680
Always wanting a better one.

618
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,310
Then letting

619
00:33:56,750 --> 00:33:57,920
the other good one go.

620
00:33:58,830 --> 00:34:01,110
Old friends

621
00:34:01,440 --> 00:34:03,680
slowly drift apart.

622
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:05,590
And those things

623
00:34:06,750 --> 00:34:07,830
fade from memory.

624
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:10,800
Honestly,

625
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:12,320
in the end,

626
00:34:13,190 --> 00:34:15,480
the one who stayed by my side

627
00:34:16,590 --> 00:34:17,710
is just my husband.

628
00:34:31,800 --> 00:34:33,800
Your dad doesn't
care about anything now.

629
00:34:35,280 --> 00:34:36,840
He just wants to see you get married.

630
00:34:39,510 --> 00:34:40,670
I'm asking you.

631
00:34:46,510 --> 00:34:47,350
Tomorrow.

632
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:49,320
Can you say something serious?

633
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:50,230
So when?

634
00:34:50,710 --> 00:34:52,710
Don't you know? Your dad and I.

635
00:34:52,840 --> 00:34:54,150
We're old now.

636
00:34:54,150 --> 00:34:56,230
Can't you tell what's on our minds?

637
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,920
We just hope you settle down soon.

638
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,840
Find someone you love.

639
00:35:01,190 --> 00:35:02,710
And live a good life with her.

640
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,440
He and I.

641
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:08,400
If you... you

642
00:35:08,400 --> 00:35:09,480
don't get married,

643
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:11,280
I just feel

644
00:35:12,030 --> 00:35:14,000
uneasy, you know?

645
00:35:56,550 --> 00:35:57,390
You...

646
00:35:58,960 --> 00:35:59,840
Let's get married.

647
00:36:01,630 --> 00:36:03,440
No matter how the world sees us,

648
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,510
I'm going to marry you.

649
00:36:06,030 --> 00:36:06,880
There's no one else

650
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:08,030
who can stop me from loving you.

651
00:36:08,550 --> 00:36:09,840
If we can't stay here any longer,

652
00:36:09,840 --> 00:36:10,920
then we'll move somewhere else.

653
00:36:11,230 --> 00:36:12,800
There's no problem we can't solve.

654
00:36:14,760 --> 00:36:16,030
I've liked you for so many years,

655
00:36:17,230 --> 00:36:19,320
and I'm ready to spend my life with you.

656
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:21,840
I don't care what others say about me.

657
00:36:22,320 --> 00:36:24,110
All I know is you're the one
I want to marry.

658
00:36:39,030 --> 00:36:40,440
You say you can ignore it.

659
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:42,280
Can look away.

660
00:36:43,430 --> 00:36:44,280
But can you promise

661
00:36:44,280 --> 00:36:46,030
